\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Absolutely, Sunil. Here\'92s a 
\f1\b professional English write-up of the methodology
\f0\b0  you used for today\'92s part, written clearly and technically:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Methodology for Tent 3x6 5\'b0 Flush Part Modeling\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 1. File Preparation and Environment Setup\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The CAD model was derived from a 
\f1\b DXF file
\f0\b0  containing 2D closed polylines representing the top-down view of the tent.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Python environment was set up using 
\f1\b Build123D
\f0\b0  for 3D modeling and 
\f1\b ezdxf
\f0\b0  for reading DXF files.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 File paths were dynamically configured to access both the 
\f1\b DXF input
\f0\b0  and the 
\f1\b STL output
\f0\b0  on the Desktop.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 2. DXF Parsing and Polyline Extraction\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The DXF file was read and iterated through its 
\f1\b modelspace entities
\f0\b0 .\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 All 
\f1\b closed LWPOLYLINE entities
\f0\b0  were extracted and converted into Python lists of coordinates.\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The extracted loops were sorted by 
\f1\b geometric area
\f0\b0  to differentiate between the outer perimeter and inner cutouts.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 3. Base Feature Creation\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The 
\f1\b largest loop
\f0\b0  was treated as the outer perimeter of the tent base.\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Using 
\f1\b BuildSketch
\f0\b0  and 
\f1\b Polyline
\f0\b0 , a planar face was created from the outer coordinates.\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The base face was extruded vertically to a height of 
\f1\b 40 mm
\f0\b0  to form the main body.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 4. Inner Cutouts\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 All inner loops (holes or recesses) were processed separately.\
\ls4\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Each inner loop was converted into a face and 
\f1\b subtracted
\f0\b0  from the main body using 
\f1\b extrusion in subtract mode
\f0\b0 , ensuring accurate cavity representation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 5. Top Red Profiles\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Selected regions of the tent were defined as \'93red profiles\'94 for additional extrusion.\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Predefined coordinate loops were used to generate planar faces at the top of the base (offset by 
\f1\b 40 mm
\f0\b0  in Z).\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 These faces were extruded vertically by 
\f1\b 125 mm
\f0\b0  to form the extended structural profiles.\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Any extrusion features that could result in geometric errors (e.g., tapering with complex shapes) were 
\f1\b skipped
\f0\b0  to maintain model stability.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 6. Additional Slope Features\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Right-side top slopes and bottom slopes were defined using precise coordinate loops.\
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Faces were created from these loops and extruded vertically.\
\ls6\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Tapered extrusion was avoided due to previous geometric constraints, ensuring a 
\f1\b valid and robust 3D model
\f0\b0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 7. Hole Features\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Cylindrical cut features were added at specific locations based on 
\f1\b X, Y, Z coordinates
\f0\b0 .\
\ls7\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Each cylinder had a radius of 
\f1\b 52.5 mm
\f0\b0  (\'d8105 mm) and a depth of 
\f1\b 10 mm
\f0\b0 .\
\ls7\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 These cylinders were subtracted from the main body to create holes without impacting overall part integrity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 8. Model Validation and Export\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Each face was validated before extrusion to avoid 
\f1\b Null TopoDS_Shape errors
\f0\b0 .\
\ls8\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 After completing all features, the final 3D part was 
\f1\b exported as an STL file
\f0\b0 , ready for 3D printing or further analysis.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 9. Summary of Key Practices\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Prioritized 
\f1\b robustness over complex features
\f0\b0 ; features causing potential geometric errors were skipped.\
\ls9\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Maintained 
\f1\b full parametric control
\f0\b0  over height, extrusion depth, and feature placement.\
\ls9\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Ensured that all operations followed a 
\f1\b top-down approach
\f0\b0 : base \uc0\u8594  cutouts \u8594  profiles \u8594  slopes \u8594  holes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
